parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the airbag warning light can indicate a problem with the airbag system, which can prevent the airbags from deploying in the event of an accident, posing a significant risk to occupant safety.
symptoms: The airbag warning light remains on constantly
the airbag warning light flickers or flashes
the airbag warning light turns on and off intermittently
the airbag system fails to deploy in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden acceleration of the vehicle can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when the vehicle is traveling at high speeds or in heavy traffic conditions.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly without warning
often accompanied by a loud revving of the engine
and may continue to accelerate even when the brake pedal is applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delayed acceleration and lurching of the vehicle can cause loss of control, accidents, or near-misses, especially when merging into traffic or navigating slippery roads.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or lurches forward when accelerating from a stop
often accompanied by a jerking or bucking motion
and may spin the wheels or lose traction.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Throttle Sensor and Electronic Control Throttle Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning of the throttle sensor or electronic control throttle can cause unintended acceleration, delayed acceleration, or lurching, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle's throttle sensor or electronic control throttle malfunctions
causing the vehicle to accelerate or decelerate unexpectedly
or hesitate when accelerating from a stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning of the cruise control system can cause unintended acceleration or deceleration, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The cruise control system disengages suddenly
causing the vehicle to accelerate or decelerate unexpectedly
or fails to disengage when the brake pedal is applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the frame can lead to structural failure, causing loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Rust and corrosion on the frame
particularly in the front passenger area and driver's side area below the front door.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front coil spring can cause tire puncture, loss of control, and accidents, potentially leading to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Loud grinding or popping noise
sudden loss of tire pressure
and broken or punctured tire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Soft or spongy brake pedal
inability to depress brake pedal
and brake fluid leakage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the suspension and steering system can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Vibration in the front end and steering wheel
uneven tire wear
and loose or worn ball joints.
